			    <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/06/ifind-rf-energy-harvesting-bluetooth-beacon/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to iFind RF energy harvesting bluetooth beacon">iFind RF energy harvesting bluetooth beacon</a></h2>
				<div class="float-left"><span class="postmetadata"><span class="date"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/06/ifind-rf-energy-harvesting-bluetooth-beacon/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to iFind RF energy harvesting bluetooth beacon">June 8, 2014</a></span> <a href="http://drop-kicker.com/category/kickstarter-campaigns/" title="View all posts in Kickstarter Campaigns" rel="category tag">Kickstarter Campaigns</a></span></div>  <div class="float-right"><span class="postmetadata"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/06/ifind-rf-energy-harvesting-bluetooth-beacon/#comments" title="Comment on iFind RF energy harvesting bluetooth beacon"><span class="date">25</span> comments</a></span></div>
				<div class="clearfix"></div>
				<div class="entry">
					<p><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/shakeit.jpg"><img class="alignnone size-full wp-image-1563" alt="shakeit" src="http://drop-kicker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/06/shakeit.jpg" width="640" height="512" /></a></p>
<p>A few weeks ago a new device entered the ever-widening <a title="Lapa – A homing beacon for your valuable junk" href="http://drop-kicker.com/2013/09/lapa-a-homing-beacon-for-your-valuable-junk/">bluetooth beacon </a>market on Kickstarter. Unlike the competition, the new<a href="https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/yuansong84/ifind-the-worlds-first-battery-free-item-locating"> iFind</a> from WeTag Inc. promises that it can offer all of the features of a standard bluetooth beacon without ever needing a battery charge or replacement.  This bold feature is relatively unexplained leading to a large amount of online skepticism.  In an attempt to cut through the controversy, we were lucky enough to conduct a short interview with WeTag&#8217;s CTO Paul McArthur.  While his response did help us to attach more concrete numbers to the company&#8217;s claims, we are still unconvinced that iFind is a viable product.<br />
