			<div class="post-1431 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-crowdtilt-campaigns tag-vybe" id="post-1431">
			    <h2 class="entry-title"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/03/despite-guarantee-vybe-misses-ship-date/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Despite guarantee, Vybe misses ship date">Despite guarantee, Vybe misses ship date</a></h2>
				<div class="float-left"><span class="postmetadata"><span class="date"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/03/despite-guarantee-vybe-misses-ship-date/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Despite guarantee, Vybe misses ship date">March 1, 2014</a></span> <a href="http://drop-kicker.com/category/crowdtilt-campaigns/" title="View all posts in Crowdtilt Campaigns" rel="category tag">Crowdtilt Campaigns</a></span></div>  <div class="float-right"><span class="postmetadata"><a href="http://drop-kicker.com/2014/03/despite-guarantee-vybe-misses-ship-date/#comments" title="Comment on Despite guarantee, Vybe misses ship date"><span class="date">2</span> comments</a></span></div>
				<div class="clearfix"></div>
				<div class="entry">
					<p><img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-1439" alt="vybe-ship-date" src="http://drop-kicker.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/03/vybe-ship-date1.png" width="657" height="182" /></p>
<p>Remember <a title="Vybe" href="http://drop-kicker.com/2013/10/vybe-abuses-crowd-funding-to-become-middle-men-and-charge-backers-twice-what-theyd-pay-elsewhere/" target="_blank">Vybe</a>? The Buzz Band <del>knock-off</del> successor loudly promised a February 28, 2014 ship date, but has now quietly reneged. While they&#8217;ve scrubbed the guarantee from their website, it&#8217;s still documented in the <a title="Internet Archive" href="http://web.archive.org/web/20131109062001/https://www.wearvybe.com/order" target="_blank">Internet Archive</a> and the <a title="Letter" href="http://drop-kicker.com/2013/11/setting-the-record-straight-with-vybe/" target="_blank">creator&#8217;s letter</a> to Ch00f.</p>
<p><a title="The Dynamics of Crowdfunding" href="http://papers.ssrn.com/sol3/papers.cfm?abstract_id=2088298" target="_blank">Over 75%</a> of crowdfunding efforts miss their deadline, and there&#8217;s still reason to believe Vybe will deliver a product eventually, so this is only notable because:</p>
<ol>
<li>They made such a big deal about shipping on time during the campaign, and</li>
<li>They are quietly hiding their failure, hoping no one will notice.</li>
</ol>
<p>We are curious to see what happens if enough backers start demanding their refunds.</p>
<p class="wp-flattr-button"></p>									</div>
